The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Monday, May 31, 2004 				 Daimler sets ambitious growth target
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Calcutta, May 30: DaimlerChrysler India, owners of the Mercedes Benz brand, has set a target of 20 per cent growth in turnover during the current financial year. The company is also expecting a similar growth in its bottomline during the year.																								Sources said the company, unlike various other global auto companies having subsidiaries in the country, has already made a turnaround with an average profit of Rs 40 crore during the last two financial years. With the marketing network and brand-building process properly in place, the company is in a solid footing to achieve the targeted growth, sources added.																								Last year, the company sold 1,581 cars and has set a sales target of 1,850 cars this year. New models have been planned to drive growth. Along with this, the C-class and E-class models will be repositioned to generate fresh volumes, they said.																								The company is also planning to source auto components and engineering works from India in a big way for its global requirements. 
